graders in that class.

66
00:06:37,959 --> 00:06:40,360
Do you want me to put them
all at risk because of your son?

67
00:06:40,460 --> 00:06:41,984
I think I'll just
find another school.

68
00:06:42,084 --> 00:06:44,484
Mrs Fanning, you can't just
take the boy out of school.

69
00:06:44,584 --> 00:06:46,526
You look after your business
and I'll go and find a school

70
00:06:46,626 --> 00:06:48,317
that sees my son as a human being

71
00:06:48,417 --> 00:06:50,317
and not just as another
problem to be gotten rid of.

72
00:06:50,417 --> 00:06:53,317
That is very unfair.
We're only trying to help the boy.

73
00:06:53,417 --> 00:06:55,777
Please stop calling him 'the boy'.

74
00:06:55,877 --> 00:06:57,643
His name is Samuel.

75
00:07:05,292 --> 00:07:08,109
We can see Ruby and Aunty
Claire at the park today.

76
00:07:08,209 --> 00:07:12,193
You can play on that swing you
like for as long as you like, OK?

77
00:07:12,293 --> 00:07:14,060
Mrs Bruen hates me.

78
00:07:15,334 --> 00:07:16,901
No, she doesn't.

79
00:07:18,626 --> 00:07:21,126
Just need a break, that's all.

80
00:07:22,585 --> 00:07:25,685
Don't tell Aunty
Claire what happened.

81
00:07:26,501 --> 00:07:28,334
I'll tell her later.

82
00:07:30,753 --> 00:07:34,653
- Mum, come and look at this!
- I can do it again.

83
00:07:35,877 --> 00:07:37,485
Sam, don't bother the lady.

84
00:07:37,585 --> 00:07:39,109
No, no, no. That's alright.

85
00:07:39,209 --> 00:07:40,984
We have to go home and see Daddy,
though, haven't we?

86
00:07:41,084 --> 00:07:42,609
My dad's in the cemetery.

87
00:07:42,709 --> 00:07:43,818
Oh. That's...

88
