birthday properly this year, anyway.

120
00:09:12,337 --> 00:09:15,037
- On the day.
- Yeah, we'll see.

121
00:09:15,837 --> 00:09:18,320
You know, Amelia,
I just want you to be happy

122
00:09:18,420 --> 00:09:20,320
and then this birthday
thing rolls around

123
00:09:20,420 --> 00:09:24,570
- and I end up feeling awful.
- I don't want you to feel awful, Claire.

124
00:09:24,670 --> 00:09:26,028
We'll be fine.

125
00:09:26,128 --> 00:09:27,195
We'll be absolutely fine.

126
00:09:27,295 --> 00:09:28,862
Mum! Look at me!

127
00:09:34,503 --> 00:09:35,703
Mama!

128
00:09:41,670 --> 00:09:44,612
- Who do we have here?
- Hello, Mrs Roach.

129
00:09:44,712 --> 00:09:46,612
You look tired, little one.

130
00:09:46,712 --> 00:09:48,946
Have you been in the wars today?

131
00:09:49,046 --> 00:09:50,280
A few wars.

132
00:09:50,462 --> 00:09:53,028
He's had a big day, that's all.

133
00:09:53,128 --> 00:09:54,654
He's just exhausted.

134
00:09:54,754 --> 00:09:56,487
Poor little sweetheart.

135
00:09:56,587 --> 00:09:57,787
Bugsy.

136
00:09:58,003 --> 00:09:59,654
Come here, little girl. Hello.

137
00:09:59,754 --> 00:10:01,920
You look tired too, love.

138
00:10:02,379 --> 00:10:03,579
You OK?

139
00:10:03,796 --> 00:10:06,904
Nothing five years
of sleep wouldn't fix.

140
00:10:07,004 --> 00:10:08,821
I'll put your rubbish
out for you, Grace.

141
00:10:08,921 --> 00:10:11,571
No, no, no. You've just got in, pet.

142
00:10:11,671 --> 00:10:14,237
I'll do it now. Then it's done.

143
00:10:53,380 --> 00:10:55,680
You can choose one tonight.

144
00:11:02,172 --> 00:11:03,614
Where did you get this?

145
00:11:03,714 --> 00:11:05,080
On the shelf.

146
00:11:11,714 --> 00:11:14,489
"If it's in a word or it's in a look,

147
00:11:14,589 --> 00:11:17,422
"you can't get rid of the Babadook.

148
00:11:20,255 --> 00:11:23,738
"If you're a really clever one
and you know what it is to see,

149
00:11:23,838 --> 00:11:26,738
"then you can make friends
with a special one...

150
00:11:26,838 --> 00:11:29,005
"a friend of you and me."

151
00:11:33,215 --> 00:11:37,115
"His name is Mister Babadook
and this is his book.

152
00:11:38,256 --> 00:11:41,823
"A rumbling sound,
then three sharp knocks...

153
00:11:42,964 --> 00:11:45,264
"ba BA-ba Dook! Dook! Dook!

154
00:11:46,507 --> 00:11:49,448
"That's when you'll know he's around.

155
00:11:49,548 --> 00:11:51,914
"You'll see him if you look.

156
00:11:54,589 --> 00:11:56,955
"Ba BA-ba Dook! Dook! Dook!"

157
00:11:58,507 --> 00:12:00,364
We might read another
one tonight, hey?

158
00:12:00,464 --> 00:12:02,830
But you said I could choose.

159
00:12:06,880 --> 00:12:09,380
"This is what he wears on top.

160
00:12:09,631 --> 00:12:12,064
"He's funny, don't you think?

161
00:12:14,964 --> 00:12:17,731
"See him in your room at night..."

162
00:12:19,339 --> 00:12:21,572
Mum? Does it hurt the boy?

163
00:12:23,507 --> 00:12:24,655
Mum?

164
00:12:24,755 --> 00:12:27,389
Does it live under the bed? Mum?

165
00:12:29,090 --> 00:12:30,290
Mummy?

166
00:12:32,715 --> 00:12:33,915
Mummy?!

167
00:12:35,590 --> 00:12:38,323
"How sweetly they sung, telling
of the happiness and loveliness

168
00:12:38,423 --> 00:12:40,490
"that lay at the bottom of the ocean

169
00:12:40,590 --> 00:12:44,090
and entreating the sirens
not to be afraid."

170
00:13:52,466 --> 00:13:55,566
It's that time of
night again. Time...

171
00:13:56,092 --> 00:13:58,450
If that's what the
doctor ordered, I...

172
00:13:58,550 --> 00:14:02,250
Oh, yeah. Yeah.
That's what the doctor ordered.

173
00:14:15,241 --> 00:14:16,441
Do you...

174
00:15:41,553 --> 00:15:42,701
Mum!

175
00:15:42,801 --> 00:15:44,535
- It's in my room!
- What is?

176
00:15:44,635 --> 00:15:46,327
- The Babadook!
- Oh, no.

177
00:15:46,427 --> 00:15:49,660
No, no, no. This is
not going to happen.

178
00:15:51,135 --> 00:15:53,785
The closet doors were closed
and now they're wide open.

179
00:15:53,885 --> 00:15:55,518
It's just a book.

180
00:15:55,885 --> 00:15:57,585
It can't hurt you.

181
00:15:58,262 --> 00:16:00,162
You've had a big day.

182
00:16:01,010 --> 00:16:02,977
You're just exhausted.

183
00:16:04,884 --> 00:16:08,651
I don't want anything bad
to happen to you, Mum.

184
00:16:10,592 --> 00:16:13,426
Nothing bad's going to happen, Sam.

185
00:16:14,093 --> 00:16:16,060
I'm gonna protect you.

186
00:17:26,719 --> 00:17:28,219
Mum, it's 9:00.

187
00:17:40,469 --> 00:17:42,495
He's not running a fever anymore.

188
00:17:42,595 --> 00:17:46,629
No, no, no. My sister's
gonna take him. Put it back!

189
00:17:46,970 --> 00:17:49,737
Put it back or it goes in the bin.

190
00:17:50,053 --> 00:17:51,953
Sorry. What was that?

191
00:17:52,054 --> 00:17:55,495
Oh, no. I couldn't get to
the phone. He was vomiting.

192
00:17:55,595 --> 00:17:58,370
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
No worries. I'll see you soon.

193
00:17:58,470 --> 00:18:02,104
Samuel, no monster talk
at Aunty Claire's, OK?

194
00:18:03,054 --> 00:18:06,487
Samuel... no Babadook.
No nothing. Alright?

195
00:18:14,847 --> 00:18:16,280
88. Number 88.

196
00:18:17,470 --> 00:18:18,970
Two fat ladies.

197
00:18:19,388 --> 00:18:20,754
Good, Elaine!

198
00:18:21,012 --> 00:18:25,112
Another few days and someone
could call out, "Bingo!"

199
00:18:27,139 --> 00:18:28,339
Number 11.

200
00:18:28,470 --> 00:18:30,121
Who has number 11?

201
00:18:30,221 --> 00:18:31,421
Legs 11.

202
00:18:32,305 --> 00:18:34,738
Hey? See what else we've got.

203
00:18:37,471 --> 00:18:38,671
5 billion.

204
00:18:39,471 --> 00:18:41,371
Anyone got 5 billion?

205
00:18:52,971 --> 00:18:57,071
Beverley's not very impressed
with your bingo skills.

206
00:18:58,846 --> 00:19:01,330
- Are you alright?
- Yeah, yeah.

207
00:19:01,430 --> 00:19:04,080
No, I'm fine. How are you?
How's D wing?

208
00:19:04,180 --> 00:19:07,346
Fine. Yeah. Just a
bunch of old people.

209
00:19:10,015 --> 00:19:12,788
You don't have to be fine, you know.

210
00:19:12,888 --> 00:19:15,655
Just a bit stressed at the moment.

211
00:19:16,306 --> 00:19:18,272
Why don't you go home?

212
00:19:19,264 --> 00:19:22,564
Old cranky bitch...
she goes after lunch.

213
00:19:22,723 --> 00:19:23,538
I can cover for you.

214
00:19:23,638 --> 00:19:25,805
- You'd do that?
- Yeah.

215
00:19:28,015 --> 00:19:29,872
I'll give you my pay.

216
00:19:29,972 --> 00:19:31,789
Oh, no. Don't be ridiculous.

217
00:19:31,889 --> 00:19:33,856
You've got a sick boy.

218
00:19:34,181 --> 00:19:35,814
Life's too short.

219
00:19:36,056 --> 00:19:38,156
You're so sweet, Robbie.

220
00:19:40,139 --> 00:19:42,305
- You should go.
- Yeah.

221
00:19:42,472 --> 00:19:45,239
- Say hi to Sam for me.
- I will.

222
00:20:36,347 --> 00:20:39,647
Where have you been?
You weren't at work.

223
00:20:39,806 --> 00:20:40,956
Rung you a million times.

224
00:20:41,056 --> 00:20:41,998
What happened?

225
00:20:42,098 --> 00:20:44,081
Just scared the crap
out of Ruby. That's all.

226
00:20:44,181 --> 00:20:47,247
He insisted on talking to this
bloody Babadook thing all day.

227
00:20:47,347 --> 00:20:49,499
Just talking to the air...
even freaked me out.

228
00:20:49,599 --> 00:20:50,539
I'm so sorry.

229
00:20:50,639 --> 00:20:51,998
You need to get him to
see someone, Amelia.

230
00:20:52,098 --> 00:20:53,916
It's not normal for a kid to
carry on with this rubbish.

231
00:20:54,016 --> 00:20:55,373
It's not rubbish. It's real!

232
00:20:55,473 --> 00:20:59,107
Don't you talk to your
Aunty Claire like that.

233
00:21:00,307 --> 00:21:01,916
Where did you get those firecrackers?

234
00:21:02,016 --> 00:21:03,832
You got them for me on the internet.

235
00:21:03,932 --> 00:21:06,898
Well, that's the end of the internet.

236
00:21:07,681 --> 00:21:10,456
If the Babadook was real,
we'd see it right now, wouldn't we?

237
00:21:10,556 --> 00:21:14,082
It wants to scare you
first then you'll see it.

238
00:21:14,182 --> 00:21:15,916
Well, I'm not scared.

239
00:21:16,016 --> 00:21:19,041
You will be when it creeps
into your room at night.

240
00:21:19,141 --> 00:21:20,574
That's enough.

241
00:21:20,807 --> 00:21:23,290
You will be when it
eats your insides.

242
00:21:23,390 --> 00:21:25,999
I've decided you're not having
your birthday with Ruby this week.

243
00:21:26,099 --> 00:21:29,332
No cake, no games.
That's the end of it.

244
00:21:32,473 --> 00:21:33,673
Samuel.

245
00:21:43,432 --> 00:21:46,199
Ladies and gentlemen, Mum and Dad,

246
00:21:47,516 --> 00:21:50,083
life is not always as it seems.

247
00:21:50,184 --> 00:21:52,484
It can be a wondrous thing.

248
00:21:53,432 --> 00:21:56,332
But it can also be very treacherous.

249
00:22:05,892 --> 00:22:08,525
Don't worry, Dad. I'll save Mum.

250
00:22:09,224 --> 00:22:12,324
I'm gonna trap the
Babadook like this.

251
00:22:15,142 --> 00:22:18,249
And when it's trapped,
I'm gonna kill it.

252
00:22:18,349 --> 00:22:19,549
Samuel.

253
00:22:29,767 --> 00:22:31,542
I was just putting something back.

254
00:22:31,642 --> 00:22:34,000
- All your father's things are down there.
- He's my father.

255
00:22:34,100 --> 00:22:35,800
You don't own him!

256
00:22:37,934 --> 00:22:41,034
Just thought I'd see
how you're going.

257
00:22:43,642 --> 00:22:45,075
Can I come in?

258
00:22:46,308 --> 00:22:48,675
Hey, matey. This is for you.

259
00:22:49,433 --> 00:22:52,125
My mum always got me a model
plane when I was sick.

260
00:22:52,225 --> 00:22:53,592
I'm not sick.

261
00:22:55,350 --> 00:22:57,050
Oh. I-I thought...

262
00:22:57,684 --> 00:22:59,250
No, he's not, actually.

263
00:22:59,350 --> 00:23:02,334
The truth is he's so disobedient
he can't go to school anymore.

264
00:23:02,434 --> 00:23:03,377
You said that's not true.

265
00:23:03,477 --> 00:23:04,918
How many 6-year-old boys
do you know, Robbie,

266
00:23:05,018 --> 00:23:07,050
- who still believe in monsters?
- I hate you!

267
00:23:07,150 --> 00:23:12,450
She won't let me have a birthday party
and she won't let me have a dad!

268
00:24:25,478 --> 00:24:26,845
Don't eat it.

269
00:24:39,727 --> 00:24:41,893
The Babadook did it, Mum.

270
00:24:43,310 --> 00:24:44,794
Go and watch a DVD and
I'll make something else.

271
00:24:44,894 --> 00:24:48,127
- The Babadook did it!
- Just go and watch a DVD, Samuel.

272
00:24:48,227 --> 00:24:51,194
Ladies and gentlemen, girls and boys,

273
00:24:52,977 --> 00:24:57,010
welcome to the great Martin's
DVD 'School of Magic'.

274
00:24:58,435 --> 00:25:01,002
Life is not always as it seems.

275
00:25:01,519 --> 00:25:03,819
It can be a wondrous thing.

276
00:25:05,645 --> 00:25:08,545
But it can also be very treacherous.

277
00:25:09,686 --> 00:25:10,986
In this DVD,

278
00:25:12,019 --> 00:25:15,986
you will learn magic tricks
to surprise, to delight

279
00:25:16,645 --> 00:25:20,345
and perhaps even shock
your family and friends.

280
00:25:45,646 --> 00:25:47,946
Do you think this is funny?

281
00:25:48,770 --> 00:25:50,270
Oh, no. No. No!

282
00:25:53,729 --> 00:25:55,162
Give it to me!

283
00:25:56,938 --> 00:25:58,571
Do you wanna die?

284
00:27:12,021 --> 00:27:14,505
Don't let it in! Don't let it in!

285
00:27:14,605 --> 00:27:18,213
Don't let it in! Don't let it in!
Don't let it in!

286
00:27:18,313 --> 00:27:19,880
Don't let it in!

287
00:28:30,898 --> 00:28:33,998
Mum, do we have to
go to Ruby's party?

288
00:28:44,690 --> 00:28:47,132
I've already got this doll, Mum.

289
00:28:47,232 --> 00:28:48,465
Now she's got a twin.

290
00:28:48,565 --> 00:28:51,065
They can go shopping together.

291
00:28:54,256 --> 00:28:55,489
Off you go.

292
00:28:57,023 --> 00:28:59,057
He's just really tired.

293
00:29:04,232 --> 00:29:06,199
Go and play right now.

294
00:29:13,232 --> 00:29:15,798
Claire tells me you're a writer.

295
00:29:15,898 --> 00:29:18,507
Oh, no, not really. Not anymore.

296
00:29:18,607 --> 00:29:21,008
What kind of writing did you do?

297
00:29:21,108 --> 00:29:24,965
I wrote some articles for some
magazines, did some kids' stuff.

298
00:29:25,065 --> 00:29:27,382
You just need to get
back into it. That's all.

299
00:29:27,482 --> 00:29:28,840
It must be difficult.

300
00:29:28,940 --> 00:29:32,300
I do volunteer work with
some disadvantaged women

301
00:29:32,400 --> 00:29:35,049
and a few of them have
lost their husbands

302
00:29:35,149 --> 00:29:37,449
and they find it very hard.

303
00:29:39,691 --> 00:29:41,257
How's Richard's merger going?

304
00:29:41,357 --> 00:29:45,124
Oh, good. I mean,
his workload's just ballooned.

305
00:29:45,608 --> 00:29:48,300
I've got the kids 24/7,
it feels like.

306
00:29:48,400 --> 00:29:49,466
Tell me about it!

307
00:29:49,566 --> 00:29:51,799
I don't even have time to go to
the gym anymore. It's ridiculous!

308
00:29:51,899 --> 00:29:53,425
That's a real tragedy.

309
00:29:53,525 --> 00:29:56,757
Not having time to go to the
gym anymore. How do you cope?

310
00:29:56,857 --> 00:29:58,841
You must have so much to talk about

311
00:29:58,941 --> 00:30:01,841
with those poor disadvantaged women.

312
00:30:12,024 --> 00:30:15,632
This is my tree house.
You're not allowed in here.

313
00:30:15,732 --> 00:30:17,832
I'm not hurting anybody.

314
00:30:19,732 --> 00:30:20,932
Bye.

315
00:30:23,525 --> 00:30:25,358
- Thanks.
- Thanks.

316
00:30:31,525 --> 00:30:33,383
How would your mum
know if it's real or not?

317
00:30:33,483 --> 00:30:35,425
She never comes to our house.

318
00:30:35,525 --> 00:30:37,925
Mum told Dad she didn't
want to go to your house

319
00:30:38,025 --> 00:30:39,800
'cause it's too depressing.

320
00:30:39,900 --> 00:30:42,800
The Babadook would eat
your mum for breakfast.

321
00:30:42,900 --> 00:30:45,342
- It'd rip her arms off.
- Shut up!

322
00:30:45,442 --> 00:30:48,550
They feel sorry for me, Claire.
There's a big difference.

323
00:30:48,650 --> 00:30:50,967
God, Amelia, as soon as anyone
mentions Oskar, you can't cope.

324
00:30:51,067 --> 00:30:53,550
- That's not true.
- It'll be seven years.

325
00:30:53,650 --> 00:30:55,010
Isn't it time you moved on?

326
00:30:55,110 --> 00:30:56,550
I have moved on.

327
00:30:56,650 --> 00:31:00,010
I don't mention him.
I don't talk about him.

328
00:31:00,110 --> 00:31:02,134
What strain is that on you, Claire?

329
00:31:02,234 --> 00:31:04,925
You're not even good
enough to have a dad.

330
00:31:05,025 --> 00:31:06,967
Everyone else has one and you don't.

331
00:31:07,067 --> 00:31:08,634
I do have a dad!

332
00:31:08,734 --> 00:31:11,509
I listen to your life
day in, day out,

333
00:31:11,609 --> 00:31:14,593
and you never stop to ask
me anything about mine.

334
00:31:14,693 --> 00:31:17,252
I do! I want to know how you are.

335
00:31:17,352 --> 00:31:19,259
You don't come round
to our house anymore.

336
00:31:19,359 --> 00:31:21,468
Because I can't stand
being around your son.

337
00:31:21,568 --> 00:31:24,093
I can't believe you just said that.

338
00:31:24,193 --> 00:31:26,634
You can't stand being
around him yourself.

339
00:31:26,734 --> 00:31:29,134
Your dad died so he didn't
have to be with you.

340
00:31:29,234 --> 00:31:32,542
- That's not true!
- And your mum doesn't want you.

341
00:31:32,642 --> 00:31:34,276
No-one wants you.

342
00:31:45,360 --> 00:31:46,469
What did you do?!

343
00:31:46,569 --> 00:31:50,402
She said I didn't have a dad.
She kept saying it.

344
00:31:50,860 --> 00:31:52,360
Is she alright?

345
00:31:52,485 --> 00:31:57,892
Stay here and look after the children
or do you want another one to get hurt?

346
00:31:57,992 --> 00:32:00,559
Mummy! She wouldn't believe me!

347
00:32:02,278 --> 00:32:03,644
Mummy! Mummy!

348
00:32:04,776 --> 00:32:05,976
Mummy!

349
00:32:06,694 --> 00:32:10,461
- Mummy! Mummy!
- Why can't you just be normal?!

350
00:32:12,278 --> 00:32:14,178
There is no Babadook!

351
00:32:16,319 --> 00:32:17,519
Get out!

352
00:32:21,236 --> 00:32:23,136
- Get out!
- Samuel?

353
00:32:23,902 --> 00:32:26,052
- Mummy!
- Stop this now!

354
00:32:26,152 --> 00:32:28,385
Get out! Get out! Get out!

355
00:32:48,195 --> 00:32:49,345
Please help me!

356
00:32:49,445 --> 00:32:52,345
There's something wrong with my son.

357
00:33:03,486 --> 00:33:06,593
I think it may have been
a febrile convulsión.

358
00:33:06,693 --> 00:33:08,469
That's when the brain overheats.

359
00:33:08,569 --> 00:33:11,677
- It always looks worse than it is.
- I've never seen anything like this.

360
00:33:11,777 --> 00:33:13,761
We'll have to wait until
the tests come back.

361
00:33:13,861 --> 00:33:15,552
All his other results are normal.

362
00:33:15,652 --> 00:33:19,486
He's obviously suffering
a high level of anxiety.

363
00:33:19,819 --> 00:33:21,470
Very committed to the monster theory.

364
00:33:21,570 --> 00:33:23,737
That's an understatement.

365
00:33:24,069 --> 00:33:26,302
All children see monsters.

366
00:33:26,694 --> 00:33:28,128
Not like this.

367
00:33:29,777 --> 00:33:31,762
And it's getting worse.

368
00:33:31,862 --> 00:33:34,029
He's becoming aggressive.

369
00:33:34,570 --> 00:33:36,054
He could see a psychiatrist.

370
00:33:36,154 --> 00:33:37,678
I can refer you.

371
00:33:37,778 --> 00:33:39,261
Takes a few weeks to get in.

372
00:33:39,361 --> 00:33:40,927
That'd be great.

373
00:33:42,486 --> 00:33:45,719
But can you just give
me something for now,

374
00:33:45,819 --> 00:33:47,852
just to make him sleep?

375
00:33:49,403 --> 00:33:50,769
Just until...

376
00:33:52,320 --> 00:33:55,020
just until we get an appointment.

377
00:33:55,694 --> 00:33:56,894
Please?

378
00:33:57,862 --> 00:34:01,562
I haven't slept in weeks
and neither has Samuel

379
00:34:02,653 --> 00:34:05,970
and when we go home tonight, this
whole nightmare will start up again

380
00:34:06,070 --> 00:34:07,220
and I am really...

381
00:34:07,320 --> 00:34:09,286
I'm really not coping.

382
00:34:12,446 --> 00:34:15,880
I can give you a short
course of sedatives.

383
00:34:17,070 --> 00:34:19,386
Just until the tests come back.

384
00:34:19,486 --> 00:34:24,053
Most mothers aren't too keen
on them unless it's really bad.

385
00:34:24,362 --> 00:34:25,928
It's really bad.

386
00:34:33,571 --> 00:34:36,405
These can make children feel foggy.

387
00:34:38,155 --> 00:34:40,305
Perhaps some temporary nausea.

388
00:34:40,405 --> 00:34:43,512
They'll certainly help
him sleep, though.

389
00:34:43,612 --> 00:34:46,512
- That's for one week.
- Thank you.

390
00:34:49,321 --> 00:34:51,487
Why don't people like me?

391
00:34:51,696 --> 00:34:53,530
Why do you say that?

392
00:34:53,779 --> 00:34:57,546
Ruby said people don't
like me 'cause I'm weird.

393
00:34:58,946 --> 00:35:02,513
Sometimes people say
things that aren't true.

394
00:35:06,488 --> 00:35:11,588
You just need to take your medicine,
have a big sleep and not worry.

395
00:35:13,447 --> 00:35:15,138
I don't want you to die.

396
00:35:15,238 --> 00:35:18,264
I'm not gonna die
for a long time yet.

397
00:35:18,364 --> 00:35:22,064
Did you think that about
my dad before he died?

398
00:35:26,739 --> 00:35:30,172
Just take your pill so
you can go to sleep.

399
00:35:30,364 --> 00:35:32,597
I've got the day off tomorrow.

400
00:35:32,697 --> 00:35:34,639
Maybe we could do something?

401
00:35:34,739 --> 00:35:37,706
Will these make the Babadook go away?

402
00:35:38,114 --> 00:35:41,597
I think so but you have to promise
me not to mention it again.

403
00:35:41,697 --> 00:35:45,640
I promise to protect you if
you promise to protect me.

404
00:35:45,740 --> 00:35:47,472
Then I won't mention it.

405
00:35:47,572 --> 00:35:49,739
I promise to protect you.

406
00:35:51,906 --> 00:35:53,106
Come on.

407
00:36:04,864 --> 00:36:06,064
Come on.

408
00:36:12,531 --> 00:36:14,765
Can you stay here with me?

409
00:36:15,032 --> 00:36:16,232
Yes.

410
00:36:16,948 --> 00:36:18,515
I love you, Mum.

411
00:36:19,282 --> 00:36:20,482
Me too.

412
00:39:23,284 --> 00:39:25,518
Her nose is broken in two places.

413
00:39:25,618 --> 00:39:27,726
- She may need surgery.
- I'll pay for everything.

414
00:39:27,826 --> 00:39:29,476
You can't even pay your own bills.

415
00:39:29,576 --> 00:39:30,851
Look, I really have to go.

416
00:39:30,951 --> 00:39:34,643
Claire, I think someone is
stalking me and Samuel.

417
00:39:34,743 --> 00:39:35,943
What?

418
00:39:36,118 --> 00:39:38,059
A book turned up at our place.

419
00:39:38,159 --> 00:39:41,686
I threw it away but somebody
glued it back together

420
00:39:41,786 --> 00:39:43,476
and put it on our doorstep.

421
00:39:43,576 --> 00:39:46,809
Amelia, I just can't
help you right now.

422
00:39:46,993 --> 00:39:49,852
I don't expect you to help.
I just wanted...

423
00:39:49,952 --> 00:39:52,102
If you're that worried,
you should go to the police.

424
00:39:52,202 --> 00:39:53,569
I have to go.

425
00:40:13,744 --> 00:40:14,944
Claire!

426
00:40:17,327 --> 00:40:18,527
Hello?

427
00:40:20,368 --> 00:40:21,602
Babadook...

428
00:40:24,869 --> 00:40:26,235
dook... dook.

429
00:40:35,369 --> 00:40:36,569
Hi.

430
00:40:38,285 --> 00:40:42,144
I want to report someone
stalking me and my child.

431
00:40:42,244 --> 00:40:43,477
Can you tell us what happened?

432
00:40:43,577 --> 00:40:46,410
Somebody sent me a children's book.

433
00:40:48,244 --> 00:40:49,444
And?

434
00:40:50,619 --> 00:40:53,687
And it contained violent
and graphic images

435
00:40:53,787 --> 00:40:55,728
of my child and me being murdered.

436
00:40:55,828 --> 00:40:57,728
Can we have a look
at the book, please?

437
00:40:57,828 --> 00:40:59,061
I burnt it.

438
00:41:00,078 --> 00:41:01,445
You burnt it?

439
00:41:02,787 --> 00:41:03,812
Yes.

440
00:41:03,912 --> 00:41:08,144
Well, unfortunately,
there's nothing we can do about it.

441
00:41:08,244 --> 00:41:11,678
He's been making phone
calls to me as well.

442
00:41:12,079 --> 00:41:13,271
What's he been saying?

443
00:41:13,371 --> 00:41:16,338
Nothing, just making these... noises.

444
00:41:17,036 --> 00:41:18,770
How do you know it's the same person?

445
00:41:18,870 --> 00:41:21,227
Because of what he wrote in the book.

446
00:41:21,327 --> 00:41:22,978
The book you burnt?

447
00:41:23,078 --> 00:41:24,278
Yes.

448
00:41:41,578 --> 00:41:42,778
OK.

449
00:41:44,286 --> 00:41:46,186
Don't worry about it.

450
00:41:55,953 --> 00:41:57,979
Did you get your things done?

451
00:41:58,079 --> 00:42:00,144
Mrs Roach has Parkinson's.

452
00:42:00,244 --> 00:42:01,936
That's why she shakes like this.

453
00:42:02,036 --> 00:42:04,936
Samuel, you don't have to say
everything that goes through your head.

454
00:42:05,036 --> 00:42:07,070
Oh, it's alright, love.

455
00:42:07,620 --> 00:42:10,853
He wanted to know so
we talked about it.

456
00:42:12,620 --> 00:42:15,186
He sees things as they are, that one.

457
00:42:15,286 --> 00:42:16,895
Oskar was the same.

458
00:42:16,995 --> 00:42:18,604
He always spoke his mind.

459
00:42:18,704 --> 00:42:21,870
Do you have to keep
on bringing him up?

460
00:42:27,579 --> 00:42:28,812
Hey, Bugsy.

461
00:42:30,878 --> 00:42:32,078
Hey.

462
00:42:32,920 --> 00:42:34,120
Hey!

463
00:43:40,248 --> 00:43:42,015
Don't come in here.

464
00:43:54,913 --> 00:43:57,230
I don't want to buy anything.

465
00:43:57,330 --> 00:43:59,297
Are you Amelia Vanick?

466
00:43:59,414 --> 00:44:00,356
Yes.

467
00:44:00,456 --> 00:44:02,939
I'm Warren Newton and
this is Prue Flannery

468
00:44:03,039 --> 00:44:04,731
from the Department
of Community Services.

469
00:44:04,831 --> 00:44:06,772
My son's only been away for two days.

470
00:44:06,872 --> 00:44:10,314
He's not actually registered
at Babbage Bay anymore.

471
00:44:10,414 --> 00:44:12,523
If I could just come
in and meet Samuel

472
00:44:12,623 --> 00:44:15,690
and get you to look at
these papers, that'd be great.

473
00:44:15,790 --> 00:44:20,490
I'm just in the middle of cleaning
up the house at the moment.

474
00:44:20,872 --> 00:44:23,772
I'm sorry. There's stuff everywhere.

475
00:44:27,456 --> 00:44:28,889
Hello, Samuel.

476
00:44:29,832 --> 00:44:32,199
I'm Prue and this is Warren.

477
00:44:35,331 --> 00:44:36,631
How are you?

478
00:44:36,873 --> 00:44:40,307
I'm a bit tired from
the drugs Mum gave me.

479
00:44:40,582 --> 00:44:44,148
Not drugs. Tranquillisers...
from the doctor.

480
00:44:44,665 --> 00:44:46,441
He had a fit yesterday.

481
00:44:46,541 --> 00:44:48,841
I'm really tired, actually.

482
00:44:49,957 --> 00:44:51,457
That's no good.

483
00:44:54,541 --> 00:44:56,607
May I have a glass of water, please?

484
00:44:56,707 --> 00:44:59,407
Yes. Of course. I'll get you one.

485
00:45:07,915 --> 00:45:09,549
It's a real mess.

486
00:45:09,915 --> 00:45:12,232
I just found this
cockroach infestation.

487
00:45:12,332 --> 00:45:13,773
I normally have the house sprayed.

488
00:45:13,873 --> 00:45:15,649
I did actually already
have it sprayed

489
00:45:15,749 --> 00:45:18,482
but there's this hole in
the wall behind the fridge

490
00:45:18,582 --> 00:45:20,348
and that's why I...

491
00:45:25,082 --> 00:45:27,650
I didn't mean a hole in the wall.

492
00:45:27,750 --> 00:45:30,150
There was a hole in the wallpaper.

493
00:45:30,250 --> 00:45:32,442
That's where they were
laying their eggs, I think.

494
00:45:32,542 --> 00:45:35,108
We've caught you at a bad time.

495
00:45:35,998 --> 00:45:37,607
I'll leave you with this.

496
00:45:37,707 --> 00:45:42,024
We're required to come back in a
week to talk through your options.

497
00:45:42,124 --> 00:45:43,624
Here's my card.

498
00:45:45,582 --> 00:45:48,015
Mum, I think I'm gonna vomit.

499
00:46:09,790 --> 00:46:14,157
- What was that noise I heard?
- I didn't hear any noise.

500
00:46:15,207 --> 00:46:17,399
Wind howling, doors slamming.

501
00:46:17,499 --> 00:46:20,732
I declare, I think this house is haunted.

502
00:46:20,999 --> 00:46:23,166
Mum, I'm gonna go to bed.

503
00:46:24,749 --> 00:46:26,116
Are you sick?

504
00:46:26,749 --> 00:46:28,249
Oh, no, Granny.

505
00:46:29,666 --> 00:46:31,166
It's only 6:00.

506
00:46:31,749 --> 00:46:34,400
Don't you want to stay up
with your mum for a while?

507
00:46:34,500 --> 00:46:35,700
No.

508
00:46:35,958 --> 00:46:39,992
If you go to bed now,
the pills won't work properly.

509
00:46:42,458 --> 00:46:45,958
You have to stay up
for a while, sweetheart.

510
00:47:01,042 --> 00:47:04,908
Where's its mother, Skip?
Koalas don't leave their babies about.

511
00:47:05,008 --> 00:47:08,058
- Are you off now, Dad?
